parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel gauge can cause the rider to run out of fuel, leading to accidents or leaving the rider stranded.
symptoms: The fuel gauge does not work
the fuel gauge reads incorrectly
the fuel gauge sticks to empty
the fuel gauge resets to half tank after cutting power and restarting.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel filter canister can cause the motorcycle to stop running, leading to accidents or leaving the rider stranded.
symptoms: The motorcycle stops running
the fuel tank is full but no fuel is getting to the engine
the fuel filter canister has stress cracks on the tabs.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel system can cause the motorcycle to stop running, leading to accidents or leaving the rider stranded.
symptoms: The motorcycle stops running
the engine misfires
the motorcycle sputters
the fuel pump and/or lines internal to the fuel tank fail.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Rear Brake Light Switch Failure due to Proximity to Exhaust Pipe
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rear brake light switch failure can cause the brake fluid to leak out, leading to a complete failure of the rear brake, which can result in accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The rear brake light switch melts due to heat from the exhaust pipe
causing the brake fluid to leak out
and resulting in a complete failure of the rear brake.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Front Brake Failure due to Lock-up
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The front brake failure can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The front brakes lock up
causing the vehicle to lose control
and resulting in accidents and injuries.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The excessive engine heat can cause burns to riders, especially in slow-moving or stopped traffic, and can lead to engine damage or failure.
symptoms: Engine temperature gauge rises to abnormal levels
engine feels extremely hot
riders experience burns or discomfort due to heat
engine overheats in slow-moving or stopped traffic.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The inadequate engine cooling system can cause the engine to overheat, leading to engine damage or failure, and potentially causing burns to riders.
symptoms: Engine temperature gauge rises to abnormal levels
engine feels extremely hot
riders experience burns or discomfort due to heat
engine overheats in slow-moving or stopped traffic.
